Class LVLFAbstractType

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.poi.hwpf.model.types.LVLFAbstractType

  • @Internal
public abstract class LVLFAbstractType
extends java.lang.Object
    The LVLF structure contains formatting properties for an individual level in a list.

    Class and fields descriptions are quoted from Microsoft Office Word 97-2007 Binary File Format and [MS-DOC] - v20110608 Word (.doc) Binary File Format

    NOTE: This source is automatically generated please do not modify this file. Either subclass or remove the record in src/types/definitions.

    This class is internal. It content or properties may change without notice due to changes in our knowledge of internal Microsoft Word binary structures.

    (LVLF结构包含列表中单个级别的格式属性。类和字段描述引用自Microsoft Office Word 97-2007二进制文件格式和[MS-Doc] - v20110608 Word（.Doc）二进制文件格式注意：此源是自动生成的，请不要修改此文件。可以子类或删除SRC/types/definition中的记录。这个类是内部的。由于我们对内部Microsoft Word二进制结构的了解发生了变化，其内容或属性可能会在不通知的情况下发生变化。)

public int getIStartAt()
        A signed integer that specifies the beginning number for the number sequence belonging to this level. This value MUST be less than or equal to 0x7FFF and MUST be greater than or equal to zero. If this level does not have a number sequence (see nfc), this MUST be ignored.(一个有符号整数，它指定属于此级别的数字序列的开始数字。该值必须小于或等于0x 7 FFF并且必须大于或等于零。如果该级别没有数字序列（请参阅nFC），则必须忽略该序列。)

      • getNfc

        @Internal
public byte getNfc()
        An MSONFC, as specified in [MS-OSHARED] section 2.2.1.3, that specifies the format of the level numbers that replace the placeholders for this level in the xst fields of the LVLs in this list. This value MUST not be equal to 0x08, 0x09, 0x0F, or 0x13. If this is equal to 0xFF or 0x17, this level does not have a number sequence and therefore has no number formatting. If this is equal to 0x17, the level uses bullets.(MSONFC，如2.2.1.3的[MS-OSHARED]部分中指定的，它指定替换此列表中RTL的xst字段中此级别占位符的级别编号的格式。此值不得等于0x 08、0x 09、0x 0 F或0x 13。如果等于0xFF或0x 17，则该级别没有数字序列，因此没有数字格式。如果等于0x 17，则该级别使用项目符号。)

      • getRgbxchNums

        @Internal
public byte[] getRgbxchNums()
        An array of 8-bit integers. Each integer specifies a one-based character offset to a level placeholder in the xst.rgtchar of the LVL that contains this LVLF. This array is zero-terminated, unless it is full. The count of elements in this array, before to the first terminating zero, MUST be less than or equal to the one-based level of the list to which this LVL corresponds. The integers in this array, before the first terminating zero, MUST be in ascending order, and MUST be unique.(8位整数数组。每个整数指定一个从1开始的字符偏移量，该偏移量位于包含该LVLF的LVL的xst.rgtchar中的级别占位符处。这个数组是零终止的，除非它已满。这个数组中的元素计数，在第一个终止零之前，必须小于或等于这个LVL对应的列表的从一开始的级别。该数组中的第一个终止零之前的整数必须按递进顺序排列，并且必须是唯一的。)

      • getIlvlRestartLim

        @Internal
public short getIlvlRestartLim()
        An unsigned integer that specifies the first (most-significant) zero-based level after which the number sequence of this level does not restart. The number sequence of this level does restart after any level that is more significant than the specified level. This MUST be less than or equal to the zero-based level of the list to which this LVLF corresponds. If fNoRestart is zero, this MUST be ignored. If this level does not have a number sequence (see nfc), this MUST be ignored.(一个无符号整数，指定第一个（最高有效）从零开始的级别，此后此级别的数字序列不会重新启动。此级别的数字序列确实会在任何比指定级别更重要的级别之后重新启动。这必须小于或等于此LVLF对应的列表的从零开始的级别。如果fNoRestart为零，则必须忽略该值。如果该级别没有数字序列（请参阅nFC），则必须忽略该序列。)
